<item>
            <title>[SUREFIRE-542] JUnit 4.4 tests skipped for a failed assumption are not reported as &quot;Skipped&quot;</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SUREFIRE-542</link>
                <project id="12317927" key="SUREFIRE">Maven Surefire (Moved to GitHub Issues)</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Junit 4.4 has support for ignoring tests at runtime via code like the following:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;tt&gt;Assume.assumeTrue(testsShouldBeRun());&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;When running tests under Surefire that fail their assumptions, the tests are reported as successful-- not ignored as they ought to be.  The javadoc for the Assume class is here: &lt;a href=&quot;http://junit.org/apidocs/org/junit/Assume.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://junit.org/apidocs/org/junit/Assume.html&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>64 bit Ubuntu 8.10, OpenJDK 6</environment>
        <key id="12810173">SUREFIRE-542</key>
