                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="14456957" author="mail@stefan-birkner.de" created="Sun, 12 Sep 2010 14:16:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This bug fix adds the method testAssumptionFailure to the JUnit4TestSetReporter&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14454724" author="krosenvold" created="Wed, 12 Jan 2011 09:05:08 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Fixed in r1058166&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14455373" author="karlmdavis" created="Wed, 7 Mar 2012 15:07:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Please note that, in order for JUnit assumptions to work as intended, your tests must be JUnit 4-style, e.g. not extend from &lt;tt&gt;TestCase&lt;/tt&gt; and instead use &lt;tt&gt;@Test&lt;/tt&gt; annotations. This is obvious in retrospect, but I just blew an hour or so figuring it out. Hope it saves someone else time.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17993861" author="olamy" created="Fri, 4 Jul 2025 07:10:53 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This project has moved from Jira to GitHub Issues. This issue was migrated to &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/maven-surefire/issues/1152&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;apache/maven-surefire#1152&lt;/a&gt;. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
